ysis, comparing diverse medieval and early modern sources. A striking semantic complexity emerges that changes the concept of St. Anthony's fire and modifies our understanding of diseases in general. This research illuminates aspects of the history of medicine, society, and hospitals.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aErgotism. 4aHistory, Art History, and Archaeology. 7aHISTORY / Europe / General.2bisacsh  aSt. Anthony's fire.  aepidemic disease.  aergotism.  aignis sacer.1 aParavicini Bagliani, Agostino, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311068955608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2019 Englishz978311061053608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2019z9783110606386oZDB-23-DPM08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPP ROW Ebook Package English 2020z978311069630140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048533312zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048533312423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9789048533312.jpg  a978-3-11-061053-6  EBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-061076-5  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-068955-6  Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-069630-1  PP ROW Ebook Package English 2020b2020  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHA